1. To do precision handling in python - 
    Use the round() function
	  round(variable_name, number_of_places_after_decimal_point)
2. To sort an array - 
	  Use the sort() function
  	arr.sort() - sorts in ascending order
  	arr.sort(reverse = True) - sorts in descending order
    After applying the function, we can print it or do any other operation on the array.
3. To convert time from 12 hour clock to 24 hour clock - 
  	a. Use the datetime library - from datetime import datetime
  	    strptime() function - used to parse the input time according to the format "%I:%M %p", where %I represents the hour (01-12), %M represents the minutes, and %p represents the AM/PM indicator
        strftime() function - used to convert the parsed time to a string in the format "%H:%M", where %H represents the hour (00-23) in 24-hour format, and %M represents the minutes.
  	
  	b. Without external libraries - using split() function
  		1. handle AM & PM
  		2. handle PM by adding 12 except if hours is 12
  		3. handle AM by converting 12 to 0

